Utility classes and functions.

This category contains helper types and top-level functions
that provide commonly needed operations like string
manipulation and data transformation.

## String Utilities

The [StringHelper] class provides methods for common string
operations such as reversing text. The [capitalize] top-level
function offers a quick way to capitalize the first letter
of a string.

## Extension Methods

The [StringExtras] extension adds convenience methods
directly to the [String] type, so you can call them
on any string instance without wrapping it in a helper.

## Guidelines

When choosing between a helper class method and an extension
method, prefer the extension if the operation feels like a
natural part of the type's API. Use a helper class when the
operation requires additional state or configuration.

